Which of the commands shows the new hard disk and what is the name of the new disk?:
The lsblk command shows the new hard disk. The name of the new hard disk is sdb

Which of the commands shows the new hard disk?
The lsblk command is still the only that shows the new hard disk. The difference now is that the sdb1 partition is displayed

Which of the commands shows the new hard disk?
df -h and lsblk both show the new hard disk. df -h shows the mount point of each partition
